==English==
===Etymology===
{{Gr.}} ''poly-'' many; ''meros'' part

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''polymer'''
#{{organic chemistry}} A long [[molecule]] consisting of a [[chain]] of identical parts, called [[monomer]]s. A polymer is formed by [[polymerization]], the joining of identical molecules. 

